lldogs.com.au|accessdate=23 January 2017}}</ref>\n* '''Vice-President''' [[Susan Alberti]] AC<ref name=\"Board\"/>\n* '''Directors'''\n\n:*[[Matthew Croft]]<ref name=\"Board\"/>\n:* Mark Evans<ref name=\"Board\"/>\n:* Fiona McGauchie<ref name=\"Board\"/>\n:* Chris Nolan<ref name=\"Board\"/>\n:* Levent Shevki<ref name=\"Board\"/>\n:* Kylie Watson-Wheeler<ref name=\"Board\"/>\n* '''Chief Executive officer:''' Ameet Bains<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theage.com.au/afl/afl-news/peter-gordon-expected-to-confirm-ameet-bains-appointment-at-western-bulldogs-on-monday-20171022-gz5qwm.html|title=Western Bulldogs confirm Ameet Bains appointment as CEO|last=Cherny|first=Daniel|date=23 October 2017|work=The Age|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref>\n* '''Chief Financial Officer:''' Wayne Tattersall\n* '''Chief Operating Officer:''' Michael Quinn\n* '''Chief Commercial Officer:''' Nick Truelson\n* '''Director of Football:''' [[Chris Grant (footballer)|Chris Grant]]\n* '''General Manager of Football:''' [[Graham Lowe]]\n* '''Recruiting Manager:''' Nick Austin \n* '''List Manager:''' [[Sam Power]]\n* '''High Performance Manager:''' Justin Cordy\n\n==Match records==\n(''Correct at end of 2016 AFL season'')\n*'''Highest score:''' 33.15 (213) v {{AFL StK}} 16.10 (106) \u2013 [[1978 VFL season#Round 13|Round 13, 1978]] at [[Whitten Oval|Western Oval]]\n*'''Lowest score:''' 1.8 (14) v {{AFL Gee}} 5.13 (43) \u2013 [[1965 VFL season#Round 12|Round 12, 1965]] at Western Oval\n*'''Highest losing score:''' 22.13 (145) v {{AFL Kan}} 24.12 (156) \u2013 [[2003 AFL season#Round 10|Round 10, 2003]] at [[Docklands Stadium]]\n*'''Lowest winning score:''' 4.11 (35) v {{AFL Fit}} 3.16 (34), [[1976 VFL season#Round 21|Round 21, 1976]] at [[Waverley Park|VFL Park]]\n*'''Greatest winning margin:''' 120 points \u2013 26.13 (169) v {{AFL Mel}} 6.13 (49) \u2013 [[1985 VFL season#Round 15|Round 15, 1985]] at Western Oval\n*'''Greatest losing margin:''' 146 points \u2013 9.8 (62) v {{AFL Ess}} 32.16 (208) \u2013 [[1982 VFL season#Round 22|Round 22, 1982]] at Western Oval\n*'''Record attendance (home and away game):''' 68,447 v {{AFL Ric}} \u2013 [[1974 VFL season#Round 11|Round 11, 1974]] at [[MCG]]\n*'''Record attendance (finals match):''' 107,935 v {{AFL Haw}} \u2013 [[1961 VFL Grand Final]]\n\n==Honours and achievements==\n\n===Team awards===\n*'''[[Australian Football League]] (2)''': [[1954 VFL Grand Final|1954]], [[2016 AFL Grand Final|2016]]\n*'''[[AFL Women\u2019s]] (1)''': [[2018 AFL Women's Grand Final|2018]]\n*'''[[Victorian Football League|Victorian Football Association/League]] (11)'''{{#tag:ref|Western Bulldogs did not participate in the VFA/VFL competition from the year 1925 to the year 2014. Premierships won since 2014 are as a reserves-grade team.|group=note|name=vfl}} [[1898 VFA season|1898]], [[1899 VFA season|1899]], [[1900 VFA season|1900]], [[1908 VFA season|1908]], [[1913 VFA season|1913]], [[1919 VFA season|1919]], [[1920 VFA season|1920]], [[1923 VFA season|1923]], [[1924 VFA season|1924]], [[2014 VFL season|2014]], [[2016 VFL season|2016]]\n\n;Notes\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n===Australian Football Hall of Fame players===\n{{Main|Australian Football Hall of Fame}}\n{{div col}}\n* [[Ted Whitten]] ([[Australian Football Hall of Fame#Legends|Legend]]) (1996)\n* [[Charlie Sutton]] (1996)\n* [[Gary Dempsey (Australian footballer)|Gary Dempsey]] (1996)\n* [[Allan Hopkins]] (1996)\n* [[Bernie Quinlan]] (1996)\n* [[John Schultz (footballer, born 1938)|John Schultz]] (1996)\n* [[Barry Round]] (2001)\n* [[Norman Ware]] (2001)\n* [[Arthur Olliver]] (2003)\n* [[Doug Hawkins]] (2004)\n* [[Chris Grant (footballer)|Chris Grant]] (2012)\n* [[Scott West]] (2013)\n* [[Brad Johnson (Australian footballer)|Brad Johnson]] (2014)\n* [[Jason Akermanis]] (2015)\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Team of the Century===\nIn May 2002, the club announced a team of the greatest players from the last century.\n\n{{Aussie rules team | title = Footscray Team of the Century\n| backpocket1