cessdate=22 January 2016|pages=22, 54|format=PDF}}</ref>\n| area_rank                       = \n| area_total_km2                  = 11.32\n| elevation_footnotes             = <ref name=geo>{{cite web|url=http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/02/Narasapur.html|title=Maps, Weather, and Airports for Narasapuram, India|work=fallingrain.com}}</ref>\n| elevation_m                     = 2\n| population_total                = 58770\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_rank                 = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_demonym              = \n| population_footnotes            = <ref name=population>{{cite web|title=Cities having population 1 lakh and above|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=625722|publisher=The Registrar General & Census Commissioner, India|accessdate=5 April 2015}}</ref>\n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 534275\n| area_code_type                  = [[Telephone numbers in India|Telephone code]]\n| area_code                       = 08814\n| registration_plate              = AP-37\n| blank1_name_sec1                = Nearest city\n| blank1_info_sec1                = [[Palakollu]]\n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n}}\n'''Narasapuram''' (or Narsapur) is a town in [[West Godavari District|West Godavari district]] of the [[India]]n state of [[Andhra Pradesh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mandal wise villages |url=http://apland.ap.nic.in/cclaweb/Districts_Alphabetical/westgodavari.pdf |website=Revenue Department \u2013 AP Land |publisher=National Informatics Center |accessdate=10 November 2014 |page=9 |format=PDF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150208134347/http://apland.ap.nic.in/cclaweb/Districts_Alphabetical/westgodavari.pdf |archivedate= 8 February 2015 }}</ref> It is a [[municipality]] and mandal headquarters of [[Narasapuram mandal, West Godavari district|Narasapuram mandal]] in [[Narasapuram revenue division, West Godavari district|Narasapuram revenue division]].<ref name=census /><ref name=map>{{cite web|title=Guntur District Mandals|url=http://censusindia.gov.in/2011census/maps/atlas/28part31.pdf|publisher=Census of India|accessdate=19 January 2015|pages=460, 470|format=PDF}}</ref> The town is situated on the banks of the Vasista [[Godavari River]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Nagaraja|first1=G|title=Narsapur civic body set to get a voice|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-andhrapradesh/narsapur-civic-body-set-to-get-a-voice/article3983449.ece|accessdate=2 March 2015|work=The Hindu|date=10 October 2012|location=Narsapur}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author1=Edgar Thurston|title=The Madras Presidency with Mysore, Coorg and the Associated States|date=2011|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9781107600683|page=25|edition=reissue|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O4VLY1KcltcC&pg=PA25&lpg=PA25&dq=narasapuram+major+towns+on+the+bank+of+the+Vasishta+Godavari+river.&source=bl&ots=IhH9MjdweZ&sig=2exgiEUfbl1Jrlx-nP0JJWI0Cxo&hl=en&sa=X&ei=LlT0VLCWHs6hugTvqYDgDg&ved=0CEEQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=narasapuram%20major%20towns%20on%20the%20bank%20of%20the%20Vasishta%20Godavari%20river.&f=false|accessdate=2 March 2015}}</ref> The lace industry is prevalent in the city and its surroundings.<ref>{{cite news|title=Handicraft exports jump 44 p.c. in November|url=http://www.thehindu.com/business/Economy/handicraft-exports-jump-44-pc-in-november/article71244.ece|accessdate=8 May 2015|work=The Hindu|date=27 December 2009|location=New Delhi}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gdwlace.com/lace/|title=Godavari Delta Women Lace Artisans Co-Operative Cottage Industrial Society Ltd., \u2013 Manufacturers and Exporters of Handmade Cotton Crochet Laces & Processed Cotton Made ups|work=gdwlace.com}}</ref>\n\n== Etymology ==\n\nNarsapur was also known as \"Nrusimhapuri\", named after the [[Lord Narasimha]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://areaprofiler.gov.in/aboutUsIntgeratedPES.do?stateCode=28&lbCode=6063&languageId=1|title=Layout page|work=areaprofiler.gov.in}}</ref> Gradually it changed into Narasimhapuram and now to Narasapuram.{{cn|date=April 2019}}\n\n== History ==\n\nThe existence of Narsapur dates back to 1173&nbsp;AD. [[Dutch people]] landed in Narsapur in 1626. Narsapur was used as a port by the Dutch and ships and boats were built here. It was noted for its ship building activity and some of the Europeans also were customers at this place; small boats are still built in Narsapur. In the 16th century, [[Portugal|Portuguese]] established their own factory which remained as a trading centre for a few years. In the 18th century, Narsapur became an important trading port. From this port, teak was exported to other regions. The ports at [[Kakinada]] and Narsapuram became famous for manufacturing ships. At present there is no port handling at Narsapur.\n\nMadhavayapalem ([[Madapollam]]) is celebrated as one of the earliest places where the [[English people|English]] established a [[Factory (trading post)|factory]] and was famous for its trade in cloth. According to [[Alexander Hamilton (sailor)|Alexander Hamilton]]'s ''A New Account of the East Indies'' (1727): <blockquote>\"Next to Matchulipatam ([[Machilipatnam]]) is Narsipore, where the English had a Factory for long Cloth, for the Use of their Factory of Matchulipatam, when they manufactured Chintz there. It also affords good Teak Timber for building, and has a fine deep River, but a dangerous Bar, which makes it little frequented.\"<ref>{{Cite book|last=Bowrey|first=Thomas|author-link=Thomas Bowrey|editor-last=Temple|editor-first=Richard Carnac|editor-link=Sir Richard Temple, 1st Baronet|title=A Geographical Account of Countries Round the Bay of Bengal, 1669 to 1679 |url=https://archive.org/details/ageographicalac00bowrgoog|year=1895|page=[https://archive.org/details/ageographicalac00bowrgoog/page/n171 99]}}</ref></blockquote>\n\nThe trade of the town has steadily declined since the abolition of the company's factory in 1827. Before independence, British civilians had made imports and exports from Narsapur.\n\n==Geography==\n[[File:Narasapuram Municipality in Narasapuram mandal.jpg|thumb|right|Narasapuram municipality in Narasapuram mandal map]]\n\nNarsapur is located at {{coord|16.4361|N|81.7016|E}} and on the right bank of Vasista Godavari River at an altitude of {{Convert|0|m|abbr=on}}.<ref name=geo /> The [[River Godavari]] empties into [[Bay of Bengal]] near [[Antervedi|Antarvedi]], at 9.6&nbsp;km from Narsapur.<ref name=map />\n\n==Demographics==\n\n{{As of|2011}} [[Census of India|census]], the city had a population of 58,770. The total population is constituted of 28,796 males and 29,974 females \u2013 a sex ratio of 961 females per 1000 males, higher than the national average of 940 per 1000. 29,974 children are in the age group of 0\u20136 years, of which 2,665 are boys and 2,456 are girls. The average literacy rate stands at 86.24% with 46,266 literates, significantly higher than the district average of 73.00%.<ref name=population /><ref>{{cite web|title=Chapter\u20133 (Literates and Literacy rate) |url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/PCA/PCA_Highlights/pca_highlights_file/India/Chapter-3.pdf|publisher=Registrar General and Census Commissioner of India|accessdate=1 September 2014|format=PDF}}</ref>\n\n== Governance ==\n\n=== Civic administration ===\n\n[[Narasapuram Municipality]] was constituted in 1956. Narsapur was made a 3rd Grade Municipality in 1956. It was upgraded to 2nd Grade Municipality in 1965 and again upgraded to 1st Grade Municipality in 2001. Narsapur Municipality consists of 31 wards and 48 slums in an area of 11.52&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://narasapur.cdma.ap.gov.in|title=About Narasapur Municipality {{!}} Narasapur Municipal Corporation|website=narasapur.cdma.ap.gov.in|language=en|access-date=27 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Politics ===\n\nNarasapuram is represented by [[Narasapuram (Assembly constituency)]] for [[Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly]]. Under Narasapuram [[mandal]], the town falls in [[Narasapuram (Lok Sabha constituency)]]. Mudunuri Prasada Raju is the present [[Member of Legislative Assembly (India)|MLA]] of the constituency from [[YSR Congress Party|YSRC Party]]\nand the present [[Member of parliament|MP]] is Kanumuri Raghurama Krishnam Raju  from [[YSR Congress Party|YSRCP]].<ref>{{cite web|title=AP Legislature MLAs |url=http://demo.cgg.gov.in/APLA/MemberReportLive.do |publisher=AP State Portal |accessdate=12 October 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022000632/http://demo.cgg.gov.in/APLA/MemberReportLive.do |archivedate=22 October 2014 }}</ref>\n\n== Economy ==\n\n'''Industries'''\n[[File:Dawn @ Godavari.JPG|thumb|FishBoat]]\nHandmade crochet lace-work is one of the most common form of industry in the town.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chari|first1=Pushpa|title=On a creative trip|url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/crafts/on-a-creative-trip/article1038504.ece|accessdate=3 December 2015|work=The Hindu|date=6 January 2011}}</ref>\n\nThere are many industries in and around the town such as International Lace Trade Centre,<ref>{{Cite web|title = International lace trade centre to be set up at Narsapuram in AP|url = http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/economy/international-lace-trade-centre-to-be-set-up-at-narsapuram-in-ap/article3790514.ece|website = The Hindu Business Line|accessdate = 11 October 2015}}</ref> Oil and Natural Gas Corporation of India,<ref>{{cite web|title=ONGC|url=http://www.godavarimahapushkaram2015.org/about-narasapuram/industriespsu/|publisher=godavarimahapushkaram2015|accessdate=16 May 2015}}</ref> Central Industrial Security Force,<ref>{{cite web|title=CISF|url=http://www.cisf.gov.in/directory/south-sector/|publisher=Cntral Industrial Security Force|accessdate=16 May 2015}}</ref> Central Marine Fisheries Research Institute,<ref>{{cite web|title=CMFRI|url=http://www.cmfri.org.in/uploads_en/media/cmfri-map.swf|publisher=Central Marine Fisheries Institute|accessdate=16 May 2015}}</ref> PanGodavari (Handicrafts),<ref>{{cite web|title=Pangodavari|url=http://www.pangodavari.com/|publisher=pangodavari|accessdate=16 May 2015}}</ref> Comprehensive Handicrafts Cluster Development Scheme, AWS (Automatic Weather Station) installed and commissioned by IMD.<ref>{{cite web|title=List of Automatic Weather Stations (AWS)|url=http://www.imdaws.com/125_AWS.PDF|website=[[India Meteorological Department]], AWS Lab|location=[[Pune]], India|accessdate=16 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n'''Aquaculture'''\n\n[[Fishery]] is one of the main occupations that generates good amounts of revenues for the fishermen. It involves cultivation of a variety of [[estuarine fish]] called ''Pulasa''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Murali Sankar|first1=K.N|title=Pulasa fishermen wait for Pushkaram to end|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/pulasa-fishermen-wait-for-pushkaram-to-end/article7453925.ece|accessdate=5 February 2016|work=The Hindu|date=23 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Culture ==\n\nGodavari [[Pushkaram]] is celebrated every twelve years in Narasapuram to take a holy dip in the Vasista Godavari River.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Hyland|first1=Paul|title=Indian balm : travels amongst fakirs and firewarriors|date=1994|publisher=TPP|location=London|isbn=1845110854|page=52|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Nebl_Xb4K_IC&pg=PA52&lpg=PA52&dq=narsapur+pushkaram&source=bl&ots=pAan79B3OQ&sig=_lW2ISr6Hp1fveUY5MfyOM2FR7M&hl=en&sa=X&ei=9905VaWGB4qO8QX4sIDwDw&ved=0CCEQ6AEwATgK#v=onepage&q=narsapur%20pushkaram&f=false|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref> This river is said to have been brought in by the famous Maharishi [[Vashishtha]], one of the seven great sages of the Hindu Mythology. The place draws people from the world over throughout the year. [[Antarvedi]], the merging of the Bay of Bengal and Vasista River, which is a tributary of the River Godavari. The place of confluence of the ocean and river is called the \"Sapta Sagara Sangam Pradesam\". It is also known as the ''Anna Chelli Gattu'' (meaning brother\u2013sister embankment).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aptdc.gov.in/blog/history-of-antarvedi/|title=AP Tourism Blog \u2013 Written words last a lifetime!|work=aptdc.gov.in}}</ref>\n\n'''Religious destinations'''\n[[File:Narsapurlutheranchurchinsidealtar.png|thumb|right|Altar view]]\n\nSome of the religious destinations in the town are, Adikesava Emberumaanar Temple, a Vaishnavite temple of 300 years old which was constructed by translator of the British East India Company, Prasannagresara Puppala Ramanappa Naidu;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://antaryami.net/darpanam/2013/04/22/sri-adikesava-perumal-brahmotsavams-narsapur/|title=Sri Adikesava Perumal Brahmotsavams, Narsapur \u2013 Antaryami.net Sri Vaishnava Portal|work=antaryami.net}}</ref> Christ Lutheran Church is in the Andhra Evangelical Lutheran Church and a member church of West Godavari synod.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiamapped.com/churches-in-india/christ-lutheran-church-narsapur/|title=Christ Lutheran Church \u2013 Popular Church In Narsapur|work=indiamapped.com}}</ref>\n\n== Landmarks ==\nThe Perupalem Beach is located at a distance of 20&nbsp;km from the town.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coastaltourism.in/perupalem-beach/|title=Perupalem Beach|author=Puja Tripathy|work=Coastal Tourism India}}</ref>. Narasapuram has become a key landmark destination for foreigners due to monkey tourism <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/world-news/crazed-gang-400-monkeys-raid-21279520|title=Monkey Tourism|author=Daily Star|work=Daily Star}}</ref>.\n\n==Education==\nThe primary and secondary school education is imparted by government, aided and private schools, under the ''School Education Department'' of the state.<ref>{{cite web|title=School Education Department |url=http://rmsaap.nic.in/Notification_TSG_2015.pdf |publisher=School Education Department, Government of Andhra Pradesh |accessdate=7 November 2016 |format=PDF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151227185018/http://rmsaap.nic.in/Notification_TSG_2015.pdf |archivedate=27 December 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Department of School Education \u2013 Official AP State Government Portal {{!}} AP State Portal |url=http://www.ap.gov.in/department/organizations/school-education/ |website=www.ap.gov.in |accessdate=7 November 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107155331/http://www.ap.gov.in/department/organizations/school-education/ |archivedate= 7 November 2016 }}</ref> The mediums of instruction followed by different schools are [[English language|English]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]].\n\nTaylor High School is one of the major landmarks in Narsapuram showcasing the Dutch and the British buildings. The high school was founded by British Educationist and local Revenue Officer H. Taylor in 1852, and was later named after him.<ref>{{cite news|title=A major landmark fallen on bad days|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-andhrapradesh/a-major-landmark-fallen-on-bad-days/article5965002.ece|accessdate=24 April 2015|work=The Hindu|date=1 May 2014}}</ref> The 'manyam veerudu' (jungle hero) [[Alluri Sitarama Raju]] had his schooling in this institution before he led the [[Rampa Rebellion of 1922|Rampa rebellion]] against the British.<ref>{{cite news|title=Alluri Sita Rama Raju Biography|url=http://www.baynews.in/editorial/alluri-sita-rama-raju-biography|accessdate=24 April 2015|work=Baynews}}</ref> [[Chilakamarti Lakshmi Narasimham]], a freedom fighter and a noted Telugu litterateur also attended the school.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-andhrapradesh/a-major-landmark-fallen-on-bad-days/article5965002.ece|title=A major landmark fallen on bad days|author=Special Correspondent|work=The Hindu}}</ref>\n\nSwarnandhra College of Engineering and Technology, an affiliation to Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University of Kakinada,<ref>{{Cite web|title = Swarnandhra College of Engineering & Technology \u2013 Home|url = http://www.swarnandhra.ac.in/|website = www.swarnandhra.ac.in|accessdate = 13 October 2015}}</ref> Sri Yerramilli Narayanamurthy college which was established in 1949 are some of the other professional colleges.<ref>{{Cite web|title = About us {{!}} Shri YN College|url = http://www.sriyncollege.org/about-us/|website = www.sriyncollege.org|accessdate = 13 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Transport==\n[[File:Narsapur2.jpg|thumb|Narsapur Railway Station]]\n\n===Roadways===\n\nThe town has a total road length of {{Convert|79.67|km|mi|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite web|title=Details of Roads in each ULB of Andhra Pradesh|url=http://centralapp.cdma.ap.gov.in:8080/CDMAAPTaxesInfo/RoadDetails.jsp|website=Commissioner and Directorate of Municipal Administration|publisher=Municipal Administration and Urban Developmemt Department \u2013 Government of Andhra Pradesh|accessdate=28 March 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160801101300/http://centralapp.cdma.ap.gov.in:8080/CDMAAPTaxesInfo/RoadDetails.jsp|archivedate=1 August 2016}}</ref> The [[Andhra Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation]] operates bus services from Narasapuram bus station.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bus Stations in Districts |url=http://www.apsrtc.gov.in/Bus%20Stations.aspx |website=Andhra Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation |accessdate=9 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160322233330/http://apsrtc.gov.in/Bus%20Stations.aspx |archivedate=22 March 2016 }}</ref> [[National Highway 214A (India)|National Highway 216]] connects [[National Highway 16 (India)|NH 16]] near [[Ongole]], a short route for [[Kolkata]] {{snd}} [[Chennai]] route.\n\n===Railways===\n\n[[Narasapuram railway station]] is a [[terminal station]] located on the [[Bhimavaram\u2013Narasapuram branch line]] of Vijayawada-Nidadavolu loop line in [[Vijayawada railway division]] of [[South Central Railway zone]]. It is classified as a ''B\u2013category'' station in the [[Vijayawada railway division]] of the [[South Central Railway zone]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Divisional info |url=http://www.scr.indianrailways.gov.in/cris/uploads/files/1404647822154-Division%20profile.pdf |publisher=[[Indian Railways]]|accessdate=18 July 2015|format=PDF}}</ref>[[Kotipalli]]-[[Narsapuram]] railway line is the important railway project to the town.\n\n===Waterways===\n\nNarasapur Port is proposed for developing it as a minor port, fishing harbor and ONGC Jetty.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apports.in/in/content/view/47/66/|title=Department of Ports, Andhra Pradesh|work=apports.in}}</ref>\n\n===Airways===\n\n[[Rajahmundry Airport]] is the nearest airport to the town which is 80km away from the town.\n\n==Sports==\nNarsapuram Football Club is part of FLOW (Football League Of West Godavari).<ref>{{Cite web|title = FLOW|url = http://www.flow.football/default.aspx|website = www.flow.football|access-date = 18 February 2016}}</ref> National level Kabaddi competitions are held every year on the eve of [[Sankranti]] festival at Kabadi Stadium, Narsapur. All India level Seniors Tennis Tournament is held in Narsapur officers club every year.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of municipalities in Andhra Pradesh]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Narasapuram}}\n\n{{Municipalities of Andhra Pradesh}}\n{{West Godavari district}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in West Godavari district]]\n[[Category:Mandal headquarters in West Godavari district]]\n", "name_user": "Sinaloa", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Narasapuram"}
{"title_page": "National Police Intervention Groups", "text_new": "{{Infobox law enforcement agency\n| agencyname      = National Police Intervention Groups\n| nativename      = Groupes d'Intervention de la Police Nationale\n| commonname      = \n| abbreviation    = GIPN\n| fictional       = \n| patch           = \n| patchcaption    = \n| logo            = \n| logocaption     = \n| badge           = \n| badgecaption    = \n| flag            = \n| flagcaption     = \n| imagesize       = \n| motto           = ''La coh\u00e9sion fait la force''\n| mottotranslated = Cohesion brings strength\n| formedmonthday  = October 27\n| formedyear      = 1972\n| preceding1      = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| dissolved       = March 2015\n| superseding     = [[RAID (French police unit)|RAID]]\n| employees       = \n| volunteers      = \n| budget          = \n| legalpersonality = \n| country         = France\n| countryabbr     = \n| national        = \n| federal         = \n| international   = <!--NNN or {{collapsible list |title=NNN |[[country1]] . . |[[countryNNN]]}}-->\n| divtype         = \n| divname         = \n| divdab          = \n| subdivtype      = \n| subdivname      = \n| subdivdab       = \n| map             = \n| mapcaption      = \n| dmap            = \n| sizearea        = \n| sizepopulation  = \n| legaljuris      = \n| governingbody   = \n| governingbodyscnd = \n| constitution1   = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| police          = yes\n| local           = \n| military        = \n| paramilitary    = \n| provost         = \n| gendarmerie     = \n| religious       = \n| speciality1     = specops\n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| secret          = \n| overviewtype    = \n| overviewbody    = \n| headquarters    = [[Bi\u00e8vres, Essonne]]\n| electeetype     = \n| minister1name   = \n| minister1pfo    = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| chief1name      = \n| chief1position  = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| parentagency    = [[National Police (France)|French National Police]]\n| child1agency    = \n<!-- (...up to 8...) -->\n| person1name     = [[Georges Nguyen Van Loc]]\n| person1reason   = \n| person1type     = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| programme1      = <!-- or | program1 = -->\n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| activity1name   = {{collapsible list |title=Engagement |Anti\u2013[[Action directe (armed group)|Action directe]] arrests|Anti-[[Armed Islamic Group|GIA]] operations|[[2005 civil unrest in France|2005 Paris riots]]}}\n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| activitytype    = \n| anniversary1    = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| award1          = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| website         = \n| footnotes       = \n| reference       = \n}}\n'''National Police Intervention Groups''' ('''GIPN''') ({{lang-fr|Groupes d'Intervention de la Police Nationale}}) are regional tactical units of the [[National Police (France)|French National Police]] located in the French [[Overseas departments and territories of France|overseas departments and territories]]. Their motto is \"La coh\u00e9sion fait la force\" or \"Cohesion brings strength\".\n\nFrom 1972 to 2015, the designation was also used for units based in large cities in metropolitan France. In 2015, the metropolitan GIPNs were integrated into [[Research, Assistance, Intervention, Deterrence|RAID]], the National Police's crisis response unit and officially became known as \"Regional RAID branches\" ({{lang-fr| antennes RAID}}).<ref>Jean-Marc Tanguy ''Le RAID - 30 ans d'intervention'', Editions Pierre de Taillac, Paris - 2015</ref>\n\n==History==\nIn the wake of the tragic events of the [[Munich massacre]] in which Israeli team members were kidnapped and killed by [[Palestinian terrorist]]s, the various European police forces decided to form special units able to fight against forms of terrorism and for other crises such as excessive use of force, hostage situations, escorts etc.\n\nThe [[National Police (France)|French National Police]] responded by creating an \"anti-commando\" brigade\u2014also known as BRI-BAC\u2014within the Paris [[Research and Intervention Brigade]] and GIPNs in the largest province cities, while the [[National Gendarmerie]] established its own unit: [[GIGN]].\n\nThe first GIPN was created on 27 October 1972 in [[Marseille]] by the [[Georges Nguyen Van Loc|commissaire divisionnaire Georges Nguyen Van Loc]] and could only intervene at the request of judges or prosecutors. It was composed of thirty men who had the latest weapons and sophisticated equipment and became the second hostage-rescue team of the [[French National Police]] after the Paris BRI-BAC.\n\nThe National Police initially formed 11 intervention groups but reduced this number to seven by 1985. This was later expanded to nine with the creation of GIPN units in [[R\u00e9union]] in 1992 and in [[New Caledonia]] in 1993.\n\nThe Ministerial Circular of August 4, 1995 established the policies of the use of the GIPN: organization, rules of engagement, territorial competence, missions, principles of actions, implementation, means and coordination.\n\nIn November 2013, the metropolitan GIPNs came under operational control of the [[Research, Assistance, Intervention, Deterrence|RAID]], the National Police's crisis response that had been established in 1985. Finally, in March 2015, they were permanently integrated  and officially became \"Regional RAID branches\" ({{lang-fr| antennes RAID}}).<ref>Jean-Marc Tanguy ''Le RAID - 30 ans d'intervention'', Editions Pierre de Taillac, Paris - 2015 pp 59-60</ref>\n\n==Organisation==\nThe GIPN were created as units of the Central Directorate of Public Security (Fr: [[Direction Centrale de la S\u00e9curit\u00e9 Publique]] or DCSP) which is the uniformed patrol and response branch of the French National Police. The DCSP has competency in 75 [[Departments of France|departments]] and within the territorial services of 7 large provincial towns ([[Lille]], [[Strasbourg]], [[Lyon]], [[Nice]], [[Marseilles]], [[Bordeaux]], [[Rennes]]) and overseas ([[La R\u00e9union]], [[New Caledonia]] and [[Antilles]]- [[French Guiana]]).\n\n[[Recherche Assistance Intervention Dissuasion|RAID]], including its regional branches comes under the authority of the head of the  [[French National Police|national police force]] ({{lang-fr| Directeur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la Police nationale or DGPN}}). RAID is also the leading unit of the [[''Groupes d'Intervention de la Police Nationale'', '''National Police Intervention Groupes'''|GIPN]] a semi-permanent force which, when activated includes the [[Brigade de recherche et d'intervention|BRI of the Pr\u00e9fecture de Police de Paris]] (BRI-BAC) and the overseas GIPNs.\n\nComposed of police officers recruited according to very selective criteria, equipped with the best and latest material and subjected to a rigorous and followed drive, the GIPN can furnish groups of police officers to the service of other police units. Each unit is commanded by a senior police officer, assisted by a brigadier, brigadier-chef or brigadier-major (within the French National Police, this military rank corresponds approximately to the [[Non-commissioned officer|non-commissioned]] ranks in the military force). He has the command of his unit during an operation, having though assistance from other participating police services.\n \nThey intervene with other services of the National police force, each time the situation requires it, with the constant concern for the preservation of the physical integrity of negotiators and only to use necessary force strictly  that as a last resort.\n\n==GIPN deployment==\nThere are three units in the [[overseas departments and territories of France]]:\n\n* [[New Caledonia]] with 16 men\n* [[R\u00e9union]] with 16 men\n* [[Guadeloupe]] (jurisdiction over the French East Indies)\n\n==Weapons and equipment==\nThe GIPN arsenal includes a wide range of weapons such as:\n\n* [[Pistols]]: [[SIG Sauer]] [[SIG Pro]] [[SP2022]] (specially developed for French law enforcement in the biggest single sidearm contract since WWII with 250,000 ordered for both agencies), [[Glock 17]] and [[Glock 26]].\n* [[Revolvers]]: [[Manurhin MR 73|Manurhin MR-73]], [[Blacksmith]] and [[Smith & Wesson]] [[Smith & Wesson Model 686|686]].\n* [[Submachine guns]]: [[Heckler & Koch|H&K]] [[Heckler & Koch MP5|MP5]], A3 and SD6, [[FN P90]] and [[Heckler & Koch UMP|UMP45]]\n* [[Assault rifles]]: [[Heckler & Koch G36|H&K G36K and G36C]], and the firm of the [[SIG 552#SG 552 Commando|SSG 551 and 552 commando]].\n* [[Sniper rifles]]: [[PGM Ultima Ratio]], [[Steyr-Mannlicher]] [[Steyr SSG 69|SSG]], [[Blaser]] LRS2, [[SAKO|Tikka T3 Tactical]].\n* [[Non-lethal weapons]]: [[Taser X26]], LBD Brugger & Thomet 40\u00d746, [[Verney-Carron]] Flash Ball.\n\nAs for personal protection, the GIPN maintains [[Kevlar]] helmets with [[bulletproof]] [[visors]], bulletproof vests of different categories (II; III; IV or V), guards and knuckles, armored shields.\n\n==Recruitment==\nOrganised at the national level by the [[Direction Centrale de la S\u00e9curit\u00e9 Publique|DCSP]], the selections take place once a year and roll within a structure [[DFPN]] (ENP [[Saint-Malo]] or [[N\u00eemes]]) with the assistance of a group of psychologists. The first part of the selection is common to all the FIPN units.  All National policemen and senior police officers may apply, as long as they meet the administrative criteria a minimum of five years of service and be no more than 35 years old.  About fifty candidates are selected and conveyed to the selected site where, during a first week, they must pass a series of events, records review, personality tests, combat ability, claustrophobia, giddiness, athletic ability, swimming etc.  At the end of this first week, part of the candidates are eliminated, and the others continue with mental tests during four days.  After finishing these tests, a score of candidates will be admitted into the GIPN where their training now starts.\n\n==In popular culture==\n* Books in [[French language]]:\n** Jos\u00e9 Nicolas, ''GIPN, Groupe d'Intervention de la Police Nationale, L'instantan\u00e9'', 2005 ({{ISBN|2-914720-12-2}})\n** Bruno Bosilo, Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Guiot, Jos\u00e9 Nicolas and Philippe Poulet, ''GIPN, Les Groupes d'intervention de la police nationale'', Mission Sp\u00e9ciale Production, 2005 ({{ISBN|2-916357-01-7}})\n\n* Written [[mass-media]] in [[French language]]:\n**''Lyon GIPN'', article published in RAIDS magazine, n\u00b0148, September 1998;\n**''Marseille GIPN,'' article published in RAIDS magazine, n\u00b0225, February 2005;\n**''Marseille GIPN'', article published in Commando magazine, n\u00b016;\n**''GIPN - Les Groupes d'intervention de la Police nationale''(French National Police Intervention Groups), article published in Commando magazine, n\u00b021, February- March 2005;\n** ''Action G.I.P.N.'', article published in Pro-S\u00e9curit\u00e9 magazine, n\u00b029, July- August 2005;\n**''Lille GIPN'', article published in Missions 112 magazine, n\u00b04, October 2005;\n**''Les GIPN, une force dissuasive'' (G.I.P.N., a deterrent force), article published in ''Police Pro'' magazine, n\u00b02, April\u2013March 2007.\n*Documentaries:\n** ''Cobra 13'', documentary on G.I.P.N. Marseille directed by [[Olivier Baudry]] and broadcast on 3 October 2001, ([[France 3]], [[Des racines et des ailes]] - Roots and wings);\n** ''GIPN, les hommes du dernier recours'', documentary on GIPN Nice directed by Nicolas Moscara and broadcast in 2003 on [[TF1]], (Le Droit de savoir - The right to know);\n** ''GIPN, dans le secret des hommes d'action'' (G.I.P.N., the secret of action men), documentary on GIPN Bordeaux directed by Claire Perdrix and David Geoffrion, broadcast in 2005 on [[TF1]], (Le Droit de savoir - The right to know);\n** ''Agressions, braquages, drogue : six mois avec les flics du GIPN'' (Aggressions, Robberies, Drugs: Six Months with G.I.P.N.'s Cops), documentary on GIPN Lille, broadcast in 2010 on [[TF1]], (Appels d'urgence - Emergency calls).\n* Fiction:\n** GIPN officers are portrayed as escorting an important prisoner in the 2017 film ''[[The Hitman's Bodyguard]]''.\n\n== See also ==\n*''[[RAID (French police unit)|RAID]]'' ([[National Police (France)|National Police]])\n*''[[Groupe d'Intervention de la Gendarmerie Nationale|GIGN]]'' ([[National Gendarmerie]])\n*[[List of special response units]]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Groupe d'intervention de la police nationale}}\n\n* [http://le.raid.free.fr/accueil.htm Unofficial Site]\n* [http://www.specwarnet.net/europe/GIPN.htm Specwarnet report (in English)]\n\n{{Law enforcement agencies of France}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1972 establishments in France]]\n[[Category:National Police (France)]]\n[[Category:Non-military counter-terrorist organizations]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox law enforcement agency\n| agencyname      = National Police Intervention Groups\n| nativename      = Groupes d'Intervention de la Police Nationale\n| commonname      = \n| abbreviation    = GIPN\n| fictional       = \n| patch           = \n| patchcaption    = \n| logo            = \n| logocaption     = \n| badge           = \n| badgecaption    = \n| flag            = \n| flagcaption     = \n| imagesize       = \n| motto           = ''La coh\u00e9sion fait la force''\n| mottotranslated = Cohesion brings strength\n| formedmonthday  = October 27\n| formedyear      = 1972\n| preceding1      = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| dissolved       = March 2015\n| superseding     = [[RAID (French police unit)|RAID]]\n| employees       = {{circa}} 450\n| volunteers      = \n| budget          = \n| legalpersonality = \n| country         = France\n| countryabbr     = \n| national        = \n| federal         = \n| international   = <!--NNN or {{collapsible list |title=NNN |[[country1]] . . |[[countryNNN]]}}-->\n| divtype         = \n| divname         = \n| divdab          = \n| subdivtype      = \n| subdivname      = \n| subdivdab       = \n| map             = \n| mapcaption      = \n| dmap            = \n| sizearea        = \n| sizepopulation  = \n| legaljuris      = \n| governingbody   = \n| governingbodyscnd = \n| constitution1   = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| police          = yes\n| local           = \n| military        = \n| paramilitary    = \n| provost         = \n| gendarmerie     = \n| religious       = \n| speciality1     = specops\n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| secret          = \n| overviewtype    = \n| overviewbody    = \n| headquarters    = [[Bi\u00e8vres, Essonne]]\n| electeetype     = \n| minister1name   = \n| minister1pfo    = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| chief1name      = \n| chief1position  = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| parentagency    = [[National Police (France)|French National Police]]\n| child1agency    = \n<!-- (...up to 8...) -->\n| person1name     = [[Georges Nguyen Van Loc]]\n| person1reason   = \n| person1type     = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| programme1      = <!-- or | program1 = -->\n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| activity1name   = {{collapsible list |title=Engagement |Anti\u2013[[Action directe (armed group)|Action directe]] arrests|Anti-[[Armed Islamic Group|GIA]] operations|[[2005 civil unrest in France|2005 Paris riots]]}}\n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| activitytype    = \n| anniversary1    = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| award1          = \n<!-- (...up to 6...) -->\n| website         = \n| footnotes       = \n| reference       = \n}}\n'''National Police Intervention Groups''' ('''GIPN''') ({{lang-fr|Groupes d'Intervention de la Police Nationale}}) are regional tactical units of the [[National Police (France)|French National Police]] located in the French [[Overseas departments and territories of France|overseas departments and territories]]. Their motto is \"La coh\u00e9sion fait la force\" or \"Cohesion brings strength\".\n\nFrom 1972 to 2015, the designation was also used for units based in large cities in metropolitan France. In 2015, the metropolitan GIPNs were integrated into [[Research, Assistance, Intervention, Deterrence|RAID]], the National Police's crisis response unit and officially became known as \"Regional RAID branches\" ({{lang-fr| antennes RAID}}).<ref>Jean-Marc Tanguy ''Le RAID - 30 ans d'intervention'', Editions Pierre de Taillac, Paris - 2015</ref>\n\n==History==\nIn the wake of the tragic events of the [[Munich massacre]] in which Israeli team members were kidnapped and killed by [[Palestinian terrorist]]s, the various European police forces decided to form special units able to fight against forms of terrorism and for other crises such as excessive use of force, hostage situations, escorts etc.\n\nThe [[National Police (France)|French National Police]] responded by creating an \"anti-commando\" brigade\u2014also known as BRI-BAC\u2014within the Paris [[Research and Intervention Brigade]] and GIPNs in the largest province cities, while the [[National Gendarmerie]] established its own unit: [[GIGN]].\n\nThe first GIPN was created on 27 October 1972 in [[Marseille]] by the [[Georges Nguyen Van Loc|commissaire divisionnaire Georges Nguyen Van Loc]] and could only intervene at the request of judges or prosecutors. It was composed of thirty men who had the latest weapons and sophisticated equipment and became the second hostage-rescue team of the [[French National Police]] after the Paris BRI-BAC.\n\nThe National Police initially formed 11 intervention groups but reduced this number to seven by 1985. This was later expanded to nine with the creation of GIPN units in [[R\u00e9union]] in 1992 and in [[New Caledonia]] in 1993.\n\nThe Ministerial Circular of August 4, 1995 established the policies of the use of the GIPN: organization, rules of engagement, territorial competence, missions, principles of actions, implementation, means and coordination.\n\nIn November 2013, the metropolitan GIPNs came under operational control of the [[Research, Assistance, Intervention, Deterrence|RAID]], the National Police's crisis response that had been established in 1985. Finally, in March 2015, they were permanently integrated  and officially became \"Regional RAID branches\" ({{lang-fr| antennes RAID}}).<ref>Jean-Marc Tanguy ''Le RAID - 30 ans d'intervention'', Editions Pierre de Taillac, Paris - 2015 pp 59-60</ref>\n\n==Organisation==\nThe GIPN were created as units of the Central Directorate of Public Security (Fr: [[Direction Centrale de la S\u00e9curit\u00e9 Publique]] or DCSP) which is the uniformed patrol and response branch of the French National Police. The DCSP has competency in 75 [[Departments of France|departments]] and within the territorial services of 7 large provincial towns ([[Lille]], [[Strasbourg]], [[Lyon]], [[Nice]], [[Marseilles]], [[Bordeaux]], [[Rennes]]) and overseas ([[La R\u00e9union]], [[New Caledonia]] and [[Antilles]]- [[French Guiana]]).\n\n[[Recherche Assistance Intervention Dissuasion|RAID]], including its regional branches comes under the authority of the head of the  [[French National Police|national police force]] ({{lang-fr| Directeur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la Police nationale or DGPN}}). RAID is also the leading unit of the [[''Groupes d'Intervention de la Police Nationale'', '''National Police Intervention Groupes'''|GIPN]] a semi-permanent force which, when activated includes the [[Brigade de recherche et d'intervention|BRI of the Pr\u00e9fecture de Police de Paris]] (BRI-BAC) and the overseas GIPNs.\n\nComposed of police officers recruited according to very selective criteria, equipped with the best and latest material and subjected to a rigorous and followed drive, the GIPN can furnish groups of police officers to the service of other police units. Each unit is commanded by a senior police officer, assisted by a brigadier, brigadier-chef or brigadier-major (within the French National Police, this military rank corresponds approximately to the [[Non-commissioned officer|non-commissioned]] ranks in the military force). He has the command of his unit during an operation, having though assistance from other participating police services.\n \nThey intervene with other services of the National police force, each time the situation requires it, with the constant concern for the preservation of the physical integrity of negotiators and only to use necessary force strictly  that as a last resort.\n\n==GIPN deployment==\nThere are three units in the [[overseas departments and territories of France]]:\n\n* [[New Caledonia]] with 16 men\n* [[R\u00e9union]] with 16 men\n* [[Guadeloupe]] (jurisdiction over the French East Indies)\n\n==Weapons and equipment==\nThe GIPN arsenal includes a wide range of weapons such as:\n\n* [[Pistols]]: [[SIG Sauer]] [[SIG Pro]] [[SP2022]] (specially developed for French law enforcement in the biggest single sidearm contract since WWII with 250,000 ordered for both agencies), [[Glock 17]] and [[Glock 26]].\n* [[Revolvers]]: [[Manurhin MR 73|Manurhin MR-73]], [[Blacksmith]] and [[Smith & Wesson]] [[Smith & Wesson Model 686|686]].\n* [[Submachine guns]]: [[Heckler & Koch|H&K]] [[Heckler & Koch MP5|MP5]], A3 and SD6, [[FN P90]] and [[Heckler & Koch UMP|UMP45]]\n* [[Assault rifles]]: [[Heckler & Koch G36|H&K G36K and G36C]], and the firm of the [[SIG 552#SG 552 Commando|SSG 551 and 552 commando]].\n* [[Sniper rifles]]: [[PGM Ultima Ratio]], [[Steyr-Mannlicher]] [[Steyr SSG 69|SSG]], [[Blaser]] LRS2, [[SAKO|Tikka T3 Tactical]].\n* [[Non-lethal weapons]]: [[Taser X26]], LBD Brugger & Thomet 40\u00d746, [[Verney-Carron]] Flash Ball.\n\nAs for personal protection, the GIPN maintains [[Kevlar]] helmets with [[bulletproof]] [[visors]], bulletproof vests of different categories (II; III; IV or V), guards and knuckles, armored shields.\n\n==Recruitment==\nOrganised at the national level by the [[Direction Centrale de la S\u00e9curit\u00e9 Publique|DCSP]], the selections take place once a year and roll within a structure [[DFPN]] (ENP [[Saint-Malo]] or [[N\u00eemes]]) with the assistance of a group of psychologists. The first part of the selection is common to all the FIPN units.  All National policemen and senior police officers may apply, as long as they meet the administrative criteria a minimum of five years of service and be no more than 35 years old.  About fifty candidates are selected and conveyed to the selected site where, during a first week, they must pass a series of events, records review, personality tests, combat ability, claustrophobia, giddiness, athletic ability, swimming etc.  At the end of this first week, part of the candidates are eliminated, and the others continue with mental tests during four days.  After finishing these tests, a score of candidates will be admitted into the GIPN where their training now starts.\n\n==In popular culture==\n* Books in [[French language]]:\n** Jos\u00e9 Nicolas, ''GIPN, Groupe d'Intervention de la Police Nationale, L'instantan\u00e9'', 2005 ({{ISBN|2-914720-12-2}})\n** Bruno Bosilo, Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Guiot, Jos\u00e9 Nicolas and Philippe Poulet, ''GIPN, Les Groupes d'intervention de la police nationale'', Mission Sp\u00e9ciale Production, 2005 ({{ISBN|2-916357-01-7}})\n\n* Written [[mass-media]] in [[French language]]:\n**''Lyon GIPN'', article published in RAIDS magazine, n\u00b0148, September 1998;\n**''Marseille GIPN,'' article published in RAIDS magazine, n\u00b0225, February 2005;\n**''Marseille GIPN'', article published in Commando magazine, n\u00b016;\n**''GIPN - Les Groupes d'intervention de la Police nationale''(French National Police Intervention Groups), article published in Commando magazine, n\u00b021, February- March 2005;\n** ''Action G.I.P.N.'', article published in Pro-S\u00e9curit\u00e9 magazine, n\u00b029, July- August 2005;\n**''Lille GIPN'', article published in Missions 112 magazine, n\u00b04, October 2005;\n**''Les GIPN, une force dissuasive'' (G.I.P.N., a deterrent force), article published in ''Police Pro'' magazine, n\u00b02, April\u2013March 2007.\n*Documentaries:\n** ''Cobra 13'', documentary on G.I.P.N. Marseille directed by [[Olivier Baudry]] and broadcast on 3 October 2001, ([[France 3]], [[Des racines et des ailes]] - Roots and wings);\n** ''GIPN, les hommes du dernier recours'', documentary on GIPN Nice directed by Nicolas Moscara and broadcast in 2003 on [[TF1]], (Le Droit de savoir - The right to know);\n** ''GIPN, dans le secret des hommes d'action'' (G.I.P.N., the secret of action men), documentary on GIPN Bordeaux directed by Claire Perdrix and David Geoffrion, broadcast in 2005 on [[TF1]], (Le Droit de savoir - The right to know);\n** ''Agressions, braquages, drogue : six mois avec les flics du GIPN'' (Aggressions, Robberies, Drugs: Six Months with G.I.P.N.'s Cops), documentary on GIPN Lille, broadcast in 2010 on [[TF1]], (Appels d'urgence - Emergency calls).\n* Fiction:\n** GIPN officers are portrayed as escorting an important prisoner in the 2017 film ''[[The Hitman's Bodyguard]]''.\n\n== See also ==\n*''[[RAID (French police unit)|RAID]]'' ([[National Police (France)|National Police]])\n*''[[Groupe d'Intervention de la Gendarmerie Nationale|GIGN]]'' ([[National Gendarmerie]])\n*[[List of special response units]]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Groupe d'intervention de la police nationale}}\n\n* [http://le.raid.free.fr/accueil.htm Unofficial Site]\n* [http://www.specwarnet.net/europe/GIPN.htm Specwarnet report (in English)]\n\n{{Law enforcement agencies of France}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1972 establishments in France]]\n[[Category:National Police (France)]]\n[[Category:Non-military counter-terrorist organizations]]\n", "name_user": "Ckfasdf", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Police_Intervention_Groups"}
